# Main/Apply.elm — EARLY

The pure state-transition layer of the Elm client. Owns
`applyAction` — the single entry point for applying a
validated action to the Model — plus the merge helpers and
the `refereeBounds` constant.

## Name audit (2026-04-21)

Previously named `applyWireAction`; the "Wire" prefix was
leaking a serialization concern. The function doesn't care
where the action came from; it just applies it. Renamed to
`applyAction` so the Model-level applier and the pure
`Reducer.applyAction` now share a shape (both dispatch on
`WireAction`, both disambiguated by their module qualifier).

## Status

- **Label:** EARLY. Extracted 2026-04-19 from the pre-split
  `Main.elm` monolith. Pure functions only; no Msg, no I/O,
  no rendering, no subscriptions.
- **Mirror of invariant:** This is the client-side realization
  of Steve's "one log, source-agnostic" principle. Every
  validated move — from a local gesture, replay tick, or wire
  broadcast — flows through this module.

## Public API

- `applyAction : WireAction -> Model -> Model` —
  deterministic dispatch on action kind, seven branches (one
  per WireAction constructor). Wire is primitives-only;
  `TrickResult` was ripped 2026-04-20 and `PlayTrick`
  (last non-primitive) followed 2026-04-21.
- `applyChange : BoardActions.BoardChange -> List CardStack -> List CardStack`
  — remove-then-append primitive used by the merge helpers
  internally. Exposed because Gesture / View code occasionally
  simulates board changes without going through applyAction.
- `findHandCard : Card -> Hand -> Maybe HandCard` — first-match
  lookup by Card identity (value + suit + origin_deck).
  Exposed because the merge helpers need a `Nothing` signal
  when the hand doesn't contain the card (replay of an
  untracked seat's hand).
- `refereeBounds : BoardGeometry.BoardBounds` — the 800×600
  with 5px margin constant. Shared between
  `Main.ClickCompleteTurn` (referee pre-check) and any future
  client-side geometry validation. Matches the server's
  constant at `views/lynrummy_elm.go`.

## applyAction branch-by-branch

| Branch | Effect |
|---|---|
| `Split { stackIndex, cardIndex }` | Calls `GA.applySplit` on board. Recomputes `score`. |
| `MergeStack { sourceStack, targetStack, side }` | `BoardActions.tryStackMerge`; on Just, `applyChange`; on Nothing, no-op. |
| `MergeHand { handCard, targetStack, side }` | `applyHandOntoStack` + `Game.noteCardsPlayed 1`. |
| `PlaceHand { handCard, loc }` | `applyPlaceHandCard` + `Game.noteCardsPlayed 1`. |
| `MoveStack { stackIndex, newLoc }` | `BoardActions.moveStack` + `applyChange`. |
| `CompleteTurn` | Delegates to `Game.applyCompleteTurn` (classify, bank, reset+draw, age, flip, advance), then updates UI-layer `score` + `status` ("Turn N — Player M to play."). |
| `Undo` | No-op. V1 has no Undo button; action won't appear in logs we write. |

## The synthetic-HandCard fallback

For `MergeHand` / `PlaceHand`, the helpers call `findHandCard`
first. On `Nothing`, they construct a synthetic
`{ card, state = HandNormal }` and apply the *board* change
anyway (skipping the hand-removal step). This is the
mechanism that makes replay of an untracked seat's moves
"advance the board but not the hand," which was important
before we added the true-initial-state replay baseline. Still
useful as defense against any other path where a hand isn't
fully tracked.

## Invariants preserved by applyAction

- `score` stays `Score.forStacks board` after any board
  change.
- `hands[activePlayerIndex]` shrinks by exactly one card on
  successful MergeHand / PlaceHand.
- `cardsPlayedThisTurn` increments by the number of cards
  released on MergeHand (1) / PlaceHand (1).
- `CompleteTurn` resets `cardsPlayedThisTurn = 0`, flips
  `activePlayerIndex`, advances `turnIndex`, via delegation to
  `Game.applyCompleteTurn`. All GameState-layer invariants are
  Game's responsibility, not this module's.

## Dependencies

Imports:
- `LynRummy.BoardActions` — `tryStackMerge`, `tryHandMerge`,
  `placeHandCard`, `moveStack`.
- `LynRummy.BoardGeometry` — `BoardBounds` type.
- `LynRummy.Card` — Card type.
- `LynRummy.CardStack` — BoardLocation, CardStack, HandCard,
  stacksEqual.
- `LynRummy.Game` — `noteCardsPlayed`, `applyCompleteTurn`.
- `LynRummy.GestureArbitration` — `applySplit`.
- `LynRummy.Hand` — Hand, removeHandCard.
- `LynRummy.Score` — forStacks.
- `LynRummy.WireAction` — `WireAction(..)`.
- `Main.State` — Model, StatusKind, activeHand, setActiveHand.

No inbound Main.* dependencies on this module should exist —
only `Main.elm` imports it.

## Tests

Currently no dedicated `Main/ApplyTest.elm`. Coverage is
indirect through:

- `LynRummy.GameTest` exercises `Game.applyCompleteTurn` via
  GameState directly.
- `LynRummy.DslConformanceTest` exercises trick plays.
- `auto_player.py` provides end-to-end smoke coverage.

A dedicated test module is a candidate future investment —
each branch's invariants would be trivially assertable.
